              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- How AI Document Management Works -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">How AI document management system Works / Implementation</h2>
          
          <div class="glass-morphism p-4 rounded-xl mb-8">
            <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Modern AI document management systems operate through a sophisticated multi-layer architecture that processes, understands, and organizes documents with minimal human intervention. The implementation process typically follows a structured approach designed to maximize ROI while minimizing business disruption.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Core AI Processing Pipeline</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">1. Document Ingestion & OCR</h4>
                <p class="text-white">
                  The system automatically scans and processes documents in multiple formats (PDF, Word, images, scanned documents) using advanced OCR technology with 99.5%+ accuracy rates. This stage converts all content into searchable, machine-readable text while preserving original formatting and metadata.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">2. Content Analysis & Understanding</h4>
                <p class="text-white">
                  Natural language processing algorithms analyze document content to identify key entities, topics, sentiment, and relationships. The system recognizes document types (contracts, invoices, reports, emails) and extracts critical information like dates, names, financial figures, and legal clauses.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">3. Intelligent Classification & Tagging</h4>
                <p class="text-white">
                  Machine learning models automatically assign documents to appropriate categories, apply relevant tags, and establish connections with related documents. This creates a dynamic, self-organizing knowledge graph that improves searchability and discovery.
