            <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-6">Implementation Best Practices</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">1. Start with Data Quality Assessment</h4>
                <p class="text-white mb-3">
                  Before implementing AI document management, conduct a comprehensive audit of your existing document repositories. Clean, consistent data improves AI accuracy by up to 40%. Remove duplicates, standardize naming conventions, and establish clear document hierarchies.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded text-sm text-white">
                  <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Organizations with clean data see ROI 6 months faster than those with messy repositories.
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">2. Define Clear Governance Policies</h4>
                <p class="text-white mb-3">
                  Establish document retention policies, access controls, and workflow approval processes before implementation. AI systems work best when they understand your business rules and can enforce them automatically.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-white text-sm space-y-1 ml-4">
                  <li>• Document lifecycle management rules</li>
                  <li>• User permission matrices</li>
                  <li>• Compliance requirements mapping</li>
                  <li>• Backup and disaster recovery protocols</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">3. Implement Gradual Rollout Strategy</h4>
                <p class="text-white">
                  Deploy AI document management in phases, starting with less critical document types. This allows teams to adapt to new workflows while the AI system learns your organization's specific patterns and requirements. Most successful implementations follow a 3-month phased approach.
